{
  format: 1
  name: ref-to-nested-collection-key-form
  suite: static
  spec: ["#state-model", "§5.4", "§5.6", "#annex-a", "§A.9", "#annex-d", "§D.1"]
  tags: ["identity"]
  note: '''Resolution (SPEC-ISSUES #26). §5.4 requires the runtime to update
'every ref that targets one of its descendants whose full identity contains that key',
which presupposes refs into nested collections. Pinned: a $ref MAY target a nested
collection, addressed by its /-separated declaration-name path (the same path root as
every other Liasse path, §C.5). The ref carries the target row's FULL identity (§5.4,
§D.1): the ordered composite of every ancestor collection $key followed by the local
$key, wire-encoded as the §A.9 composite array in ancestor-then-local order. Here
links.office resolves to /companies/offices and carries the composite (companies.id,
office.id). The package loads. (The composite key TYPE is an internal type property a
static load does not surface directly; the load-success outcome and the ancestor-then-
local composite are gated at the model layer.)'''

  package: {
    $liasse: 1
    $app: "t.nestedref@1.0.0"
    $model: {
      companies: {
        $key: "id"
        id: "text"
        offices: {
          $key: "id"
          id: "text"
        }
      }
      links: {
        $key: "id"
        id: "text"
        office: { $ref: "/companies/offices" }
      }
    }
  }

  expect: {
    outcome: ok
  }
}
